{
  "texts": [
    "So users need to either collect the training data in the form of instructions or could leverage prompt template libraries like prompt-engine-py or dynamic prompts to take normal datasets and convert them into instruction datasets for fine-tuning.2) Task specific Fine-tuning: This technique [51] involves the users fine-tuning a pre-trained Gen-AI model to perform a specific kind of task in mind.",
    "For example, the users might fine-tune the pre-trained LLM to perform sentiment detection given an input prompt.",
    "It involves very few examples for the LLM to train on, but still requires a decent amount of compute as the entire model needs to be loaded into memory for the training part.Task specific fine-tuning [51] is prone to exhibit a phenomenon called catastrophic forgetting.",
    "In catastrophic forgetting, the underlying LLM has forgotten the knowledge of the world it had obtained as part of its pre-training and its performance on the other tasks after task specific fine-tuning is much worse than its performance on the same tasks before fine-tuning.",
    "In order to circumvent the issue of catastrophic forgetting, users can employ multi-task instruction fine-tuning or employ parameter efficient fine-tuning described in section IV-B3.3) Parameter Efficient Fine-tuning: Instruction Fine-Tuning IV-B1 or Task specific fine-tuning IV-B2 are resource intensive and are plagued with catastrophic forgetting."
  ]
}